Class RangedListView<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • handist.collections.RangedList<T>
      • handist.collections.RangedListView<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type handled by the RangedListView this instance provides access to
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, Serializable, Iterable<T>

    public class RangedListView<T>
extends RangedList<T>
implements Serializable, com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable
    RangedListView provides an access to a Chunk restricted to a specific range.

    • Constructor Detail

      • RangedListView

        public RangedListView(RangedList<T> base,
                      LongRange range)
        Creates a new RangedListView which grants access to the provided RangedList only on the specified range.

        The provided base can either be a Chunk or an existing RangedListView, in which case the Chunk base of this RangedListView will be extracted.

        Parameters:
        base - RangedList this instance will control access to
        range - the range of indices that the created instance allows access to

        public boolean contains(Object o)
        Checks if the provided object is contained in the RangedList this instance provided access to on the specific indices this instance allows access to. If the underlying RangedList contains the specified object at an index that this RangedListView does not grant access to, this method will return false
        Specified by:
